Mamelodi Sundowns coach Pitso Mosimane is allegedly considering his departure from the PSL champions due to deepening tensions in his relationship with the club management. Sunday World learnt from three club officials that despite the club's success on the pitch, trouble has been brewing at Chloorkop over the past few years due to issues Mosimane has been unhappy about. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD 